# Rendered by Dev10x:gh-review-setup. Lessons-learned self-improvement loop.
# Embeds the four mandatory guardrails: scope-lock, sanitization, size
# budgets, single-open-draft-PR lock. Capable tier required (commits + PR).
name: Claude Lessons Learned

on:
  pull_request:
    types: [closed]

permissions:
  contents: write
  pull-requests: write

jobs:
  lessons:
    # Skip drafts and reverts; analyze substantive closed PRs.
    if: github.event.pull_request.merged == true
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
        with:
          fetch-depth: 0
          ref: {{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}

      - name: Analyze closed PR and apply lessons
        uses: {{ACTION_REF}}
        with:
          anthropic_api_key: ${{ secrets.{{REVIEW_KEY}} }}
          # Capable tier: this step commits and opens a PR. Cheap tiers tend
          # to exit silently mid-task on git ops — keep on {{MODEL_CAPABLE}}.
          claude_args: "--model {{MODEL_CAPABLE}}"
          prompt: |
            Analyze closed PR #${{ github.event.pull_request.number }} in
            ${{ github.repository }} for review-process lessons, then feed
            durable improvements back into the project's review rules.

            ## Phase A — Analyze
            Read the PR diff, comments, and reviews. Identify review feedback
            patterns: which suggestions recurred, which were accepted vs
            rejected. Produce a short lessons report and post it as a PR
            comment (ephemeral — provenance lives in git blame, not in the
            rules you write).

            ## Phase B — Apply (scope-locked)
            For each candidate improvement, pass ALL four value filters or
            drop it:
              1. Deduplication — target file already covers it → skip.
              2. Recurrence — pattern in ≥2 PRs, not a one-off → skip if not.
              3. Actionability — concrete check, not vague advice → skip.
              4. Budget — would exceed the file's size budget → skip.
            Apply only if ≥2 candidates survive; otherwise open no PR.

            ### Scope-lock (HARD) — you may modify ONLY:
{{LESSONS_ALLOWLIST}}
            NEVER touch skills/, .github/workflows/, bin/, hooks/, commands/,
            or application source. Abort the PR if a change falls outside the
            allowlist.

            ### Sanitization (HARD)
            Before committing rule text, strip every project-identifying
            string from BOTH prose and code examples (org/repo names,
            vendor/domain nouns, sibling-service names). Distil the
            trade-off, never the anecdote. Do not write "PR #N showed…".

            ### Size budgets (HARD)
{{SIZE_BUDGETS}}
            A change that would exceed a budget is skipped (or condense
            first).

            ### Single open draft-PR lock (HARD)
            Use the fixed branch `claude/lessons-learned`. Before creating a
            PR, check for an existing open PR from that branch and UPDATE it
            in place instead of opening a parallel one. Open as DRAFT,
            target {{DEFAULT_BRANCH}}, label `rules-maintenance`. Never
            auto-merge — a human approves.
{{SLACK_NOTIFY_BLOCK}}
